<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="81" pageId="2" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="2" pageNumber="79">
Length 6.3-6.5 mm, width 2.5 mm. Head and prothorax red; elytra black or sometimes bluish black. Labrum (Fig. 1) semicircular in front, shortly depressed towards base, front pair of setae small and closely placed along the front margin, intermediate one at a distance from margin; ligula rectangular, with a wide and deep median impression, a pair of setae at a distance form apex depressed at base; apex truncate, outer apical angles rounded; mentum (Fig. 9) glabrous at base, 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="80" start="start">both</pageBreakToken>
tooth and lobes elongate, slender and sharp at apex; tooth almost as long as lobes, two pairs of setae on base; lobes sinuate at a distance from apex along outer margin; maxillary palpi (Fig. 17) not dilated. Elytra without spots.
</paragraph>
